race.comment: CHEST OF GOLD (2) looks well placed, especially coming back to 1400m. Fancy the mile sees him out having placed over that trip his past couple, winning well in town over this trip prior. He's started favourite his past two with an ominous starting price profile throughout his career, and this looks an ideal race to bounce back to form. ROUSSILLON (4) was a surprise winner when last seen at Ballarat but did it impressively on that occasion, beating a decent field in this grade. Have to respect again now. MISS PLAYLOUNGE (15) did enough fresh at Sale over 1212m and will be fitter for the rise in trip. She draws for every chance. SUGAR COAT (8) hasn't been far away in two runs back and the fresh run in good company reads especially well.
